# ── Firebase configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com and create a project.
# 2. Add a Web app to the project (Project Settings → Your apps → </>).
# 3. Copy the firebaseConfig values shown into the variables below.
# 4. Enable Authentication → Sign-in method → Google.
# 5. Enable Firestore Database → Start in production mode.
#    Then deploy the security rules from firestore.rules.
#
# For Vercel deployment: add these same variables in
# Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# These values are safe to include in client-side code — Firebase is designed
# this way. Security is enforced by Firestore Security Rules, not by keeping
# these values secret.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.firebasestorage.app
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id
